        "title": "Java - how to return a null in this String method?",
        "body": "<p>How to make this string return a null if we put <code>things = null<\/code><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Test {\nstatic String concatAll(Object[] things) {\n\n    StringBuffer result = new StringBuffer();\n    for (int i = 0; i &lt; things.length; i++) {\n       result.append( things[i] );\n    }\n    String x = result.toString();\n    return x;\n\n}\n\n\npublic static void main(String [] args)\n{\n\n\n    Object[] obj = {19, \"abc\", \" \", 3.5};\n    System.out.println(concatAll(obj)); \n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>}<\/p>\n\n<p>this code will print <\/p>\n\n<p>19abc 3.5<\/p>\n\n<p>when i put <code>obj = null<\/code> in the main method  this code is not working, Why?<\/p>\n",
