            "last_activity_date": 1389982429,
            "creation_date": 1389982123,
            "body": "<p>Your code as it stands try's to index into the <code>Object<\/code> array without checking for null with the code <code>things.length<\/code>, which will throw a <code>NullPointerException<\/code> because there is no array object in existence, so the length field also does not exist.<\/p>\n\n<p>To fix this use an if statement!<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>static String concatAll(Object[] things) {\nif(things == null) {\n    return null;\n}\n...continue code....\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>This will first check <code>things<\/code> for a null  value BEFORE executing code that could throw an exception.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 21192863,
            "question_id": 21192788,
            "last_edit_date": 1389982429
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/kBemd.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 3507345,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 3096507,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3096507/ansible",
                "reputation": 3579,
                "display_name": "ansible"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1389982135,
            "creation_date": 1389982135,
            "body": "<p>Calling a method on a null object causes a <code>NullPointerException<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>In your case if obj = null, then when you call concatAll, things will be null as well. You then try and call things.length which is not valid on a null object.<\/p>\n\n<p>You can make this method safer by checking the input of strings first. What you want to do exactly will depend on your situation, but here is one example.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>static String concatAll(Object[] things) {\n\n    if (things == null)\n    {\n        return \"\";\n    }\n\n    StringBuffer result = new StringBuffer();\n    for (int i = 0; i &lt; things.length; i++) {\n       result.append( things[i] );\n    }\n    String x = result.toString();\n    return x;\n\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 21192868,
            "question_id": 21192788
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/wXAK9.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 1920143,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1731862,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1731862/ankur-shanbhag",
                "reputation": 7804,
                "display_name": "Ankur Shanbhag",
                "accept_rate": 71
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1389982010,
            "creation_date": 1389982010,
            "body": "<p>Here it is:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>    static String concatAll(Object[] things) {\n      if(null == things) {\n        return null;\n      }\n     //Rest of the code goes here\n    }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 21192836,
            "question_id": 21192788
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c04cd0f729410f738be9a3799f0cad8f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1363463,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1300388,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1300388/raju-rathore",
                "reputation": 149,
                "display_name": "Raju Rathore"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1389982060,
            "creation_date": 1389982060,
            "body": "<pre><code>    if(null!=things)\n    {\n     for (int i = 0; i &lt; things.length; i++) {\n           result.append( things[i] );\n        }\n        String x = result.toString();\n        return x;\n    }else {\n    return null;\n    }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 21192847,
            "question_id": 21192788
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/eeec80237213c91e5bab56b77ac5b8ca?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 16878,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 37213,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/37213/duffymo",
                "reputation": 309604,
                "display_name": "duffymo",
                "accept_rate": 81
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1389982105,
            "creation_date": 1389982105,
            "body": "<p>I'd check to make sure that the array wasn't null before using it:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Test {\n\n    static String concatAll(Object[] things) {\n        StringBuffer result = new StringBuffer();\n        if (things != null) {\n            for (int i = 0; i &lt; things.length; i++) {\n                result.append( things[i] );\n            }\n        }\n        return result.toString();\n    }\n\n    public static void main(String [] args) {\n        Object[] obj = {19, \"abc\", \" \", 3.5};\n        System.out.println(concatAll(obj)); \n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I'd also recommend that you pay attention to formatting.  Style matters.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 21192856,
            "question_id": 21192788
        }
